  "prompt": "Where are Samsung phones made?",
  "response": "Samsung phones are manufactured in various locations around the world. The main production facilities are located in:\n\n1. **South Korea**: Samsung's home country has several manufacturing plants for smartphones and other electronics.\n2. **Vietnam**: A significant portion of Samsung's smartphone production takes place in Vietnam, where they have large factories employing thousands of workers.\n3. **India**: Samsung has a major manufacturing facility in Noida, which is one of the largest smartphone manufacturing plants in the world.\n4. **China**: Although production has been decreasing in China in recent years, some manufacturing still occurs there.\n5. **Other Locations**: Samsung also has smaller operations in other countries, including the United States and Brazil, primarily for assembly and component production.\n\nThe specific locations can vary depending on the model and the demand for particular phones.",
